description:
TimeSettings: This table stores time configuration settings for different cells in a radio access network, specifying time zone, daylight saving time parameters, and other relevant information for each cell.

dateTime: Timestamp indicating when the time settings were recorded.
Area_Name: Name of the geographic area where the cell is located (e.g., NR_Balikpapan).
CellId: Unique identifier for the cell site.
Id2: Redundant identifier for the cell site (appears to be identical to CellId).
Id3: An additional, seemingly unused, identifier.
vsDataType: Type of data, indicating the data relates to time settings.
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the Ericsson-specific data format.
TimeSettings.gpsToUtcLeapSecondsChangeDate: Date of the last leap second adjustment (appears unused).
TimeSettings.gpsToUtcLeapSeconds: Number of leap seconds to adjust from GPS time to UTC (currently 0).
TimeSettings.daylightSavingTimeStartDate: Start date of daylight saving time (appears unused).
TimeSettings.daylightSavingTimeEndDate: End date of daylight saving time (appears unused).
TimeSettings.timeSettingsId: Unique identifier for the time setting configuration.
TimeSettings.timeOffset: UTC offset for the cell.
TimeSettings.daylightSavingTimeOffset: Offset applied during daylight saving time.
